com.hci.geotagger.cache
Class CacheDatabase

java.lang.Object
  SQLiteOpenHelper
      com.hci.geotagger.cache.CacheDatabase

public class CacheDatabase
extends SQLiteOpenHelper

The CacheDatabase class contains definitions and methods that are used to access the Geotagger Cache Database. This database is a close representation of the Geotagger server database with additional tables and fields to maintain a caching relation between the mobile device and the server database. The CacheDatabase class extends the SQLiteOpenHelper class.

Author:
Paul Cushman

addActionCache

public long addActionCache(String url,
                           String action)
This method will add an Action record to the cache. The input string represents a database action to be performed later. This method will NOT associate a post action string with the cached action. The addActionCache(CacheAction) function should be used instead of this one.

Parameters:
url - The URL string associated with the database operation.
action - The string representation of a pending database operation
Returns:
The row ID of the inserted Action cache records is returned

getnextTagCacheID

public long getnextTagCacheID()
This method will return the next "cache" id to use for the Tag record type. Cache IDs are negative values and start at CACHE_ID_START and decrease from there.

Returns:
A value of CACHE_ID_START and lower is returned
